<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,368,392]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by short and slim style apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1166,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 19. M" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[244,1339,939,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[188,1398,913,1896]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 19. M. pileiformis sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206134/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1138,1166,367,391]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
D) and the ventral triangular membranous area at the apex of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[738,820,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 19. M" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[244,1339,939,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[188,1398,913,1896]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 19. M. pileiformis sp. nov. A: male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus and connective, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206134/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[791,820,404,428]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1274,439,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[197,1274,439,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,440,464]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
This name is based on the triangular membranous area on the apex of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
